<statement>
<image width="33%" pi:generated="problems/images/mom-1057112-1.png"/><p>
Suppose a = 10 and A = 50 degrees. Calculate:</p>
<p>
<m>\displaystyle{b}\approx</m> <input type="text" style="width:5.8ch" name="qn1000" id="qn1000" value="" autocomplete="off" aria-label="Question 1 Part 1 of 3" class="text"/></p>
<p>
<m>\displaystyle{c}\approx</m> <input type="text" style="width:5.8ch" name="qn1001" id="qn1001" value="" autocomplete="off" aria-label="Question 1 Part 2 of 3" class="text"/></p>
<p>
<m>\displaystyle{B}\approx</m> <input type="text" style="width:5.8ch" name="qn1002" id="qn1002" value="" autocomplete="off" aria-label="Question 1 Part 3 of 3" class="text"/> degrees</p>
<p>
Round all answers to one decimal place.  Give angles in <em>degrees</em>
</p>
</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li>8.4</li><li>13.1</li><li>40.0</li></ul></p><p>First calculate the length of the other leg.</p>
<p>For the length of the other leg,</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{\tan{{\left({50}\right)}}}=\frac{{10}}{{b}}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{b}=\frac{{10}}{{\tan{{\left({50}\right)}}}}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{b}\approx{8.3909963117728}\approx{8.4}</m>.</p>
<p>For the third side</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{c}^{{2}}={10}^{{2}}+{8.3909963117728}^{{2}}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{c}^{{2}}={100}+{70.408819104185}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{c}^{{2}}={170.40881910418}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{c}=\sqrt{{{170.40881910418}}}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{c}\approx{13.054072893323}\approx{13.1}</m>.</p>
<p>For angle B</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{B}={180}^{\circ}-{90}^{\circ}-{50}^{\circ}\approx{40}^{\circ}</m></p>

</solution>
</myopenmath>